Nike Popoola Pan-African financial institution, United Bank for Africa Group Plc, says its profit before tax rose to N32.7bn in the first quarter of the 2020 financial year. The bank disclosed that its unaudited results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2020 showed double-digit improvement across all its major income lines. It stated, “The bank leveraged modest growth in both interest and non-interest income as well as increased efficiency to deliver an impressive 8.5 per cent year-on-year growth in profit before tax in the first three months of 2020, to N32.7bn compared with N30.2bn recorded in the first quarter of 2019. “Again, UBA sustained its strong profitability recording an annualised 20 per cent return on average equity.” Driven by a year-on-year growth in interest income, it added that UBA Group recorded 11.8 per cent year-on-year growth in gross earnings to close at N147.2bn for the three months period ending March 2020, compared to N131.7bn recorded in the first three months of the year 2019. The bank’s total assets also rose by 13.4 per cent to N6.4tn in the period under review, compared to N5.6tn recorded at the end of the 2019 financial; while shareholders’ funds grew to N612.6bn from N597.9bn in the same period. The Group Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer, United Bank for Africa, Plc, Mr Kennedy Uzoka, expressed satisfaction with the bank’s performance. He said, “The double-digit growth in the top-line testifies to the resilience of our business model as a group.” Copyright PUNCH.
